* Five chemicals were found via their CAS numbers, however upon Mk1 eyeball and visualisation in
DataWarrior, they are either large peptides, metallic, or inorganics. They are also all Ames negatives, and so
the hassle to process them as large molecules or inevitably remove them as metallic or inorganic doesn't
seem worth it, given there are many other readily usable chemicals in the (negative-biased) datasets.
Therefore, the decision was made to not re-include them.
